cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on improving syntactic projection and parsing for resource-poor languages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for detecting patterns, which suggests it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions using neural networks, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses using annotated data for improving parsing, which could potentially fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
